Kathryn Soderholm <kathryn.soderholm@gmail.com>

******
[2] Sao Paulo state
Date: Wed 24 Jan 2018
Source: G1 [in Portuguese trans. Mod.TY, edited]
https://g1.globo.com/sp/sorocaba-jundiai/noticia/estado-confirma-2-morte-de-macaco-por-febre-amarela-em-votorantim.ghtml


The state Secretariat of Health confirmed the 2nd yellow fever death of a monkey in Votorantim (Sao Paulo [state]). In total, 8 dead primates were collected in the Matão Park since the beginning of the year [2018], which motivated the expansion of vaccination [for humans] against the disease.

According to the epidemiological bulletin issued by the Secretariat, updated this Monday (22 [Jan 2018]), 530 infected monkeys died of this yellow fever virus infection in the state since last year [2017], 153 just in the Sorocaba and Jundai regions.

The number of monkeys dead of yellow fever (data from the State Secretariat of Health):

City / Dead monkeys 2017/2018
Campo Limpo Paulista / 13
Itatiba / 17
Jarinu / 20
Jundiaí / 72
Mairinque / 7
Piedade / 3
São Roque / 19
Votorantim / 2
TOTAL / 153

